cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SE, cs.CY 

The paper proposes two practical ARQ-based security schemes for Wi-Fi and RFID networks, which aim to enhance the confidentiality and authenticity functions of these networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed schemes in Wi-Fi networks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis and key update mechanisms, which may fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SE (Software Engineering), respectively. Finally, the proposed RFID authentication protocol may also relate to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
